 <br>
Being one of those classes that likes sword and board (an SK) -what do the rest of the FV people think about this one? I'd like better protection to go with the decreased damage I get switching to a 1H weapon...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2053<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/03 7:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> One of the things they also said ..</span><hr size=1> .. was that there wouldn't be any improvements for shield use for classes that have no penalty associated with using them; ie. if you can't duel-wield, don't expect any bonus.  Pal/SK are already supposedly blanced for not having dual wield by have some VERY nice 1H weapons that dual-wielding classes can't use.<br>
<br>
IMHO, what they seem to be trying to do is boost war tanking to the point where they can then undo the monk nerf and justify the whole thing as a necessary change to maintain relative class balance.  Personally, I think their reasoning is oh, a teeny tiny bit impaired.  I think wars with more taunt and tanking is good regardless.<br>
<br>
The pure melee classes (and Paladins) mostly can't solo nearly as well as hybrids.  As such, they should bring far more to a group than hybrids.  Paladins are already taken care of for grouping -- they make really nice healers.  Pretty much as good as a druid and much better for CC than other hybrids.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I mostly see it as a lot of noise to cover an admission that they screwed up on the monk nerf.  This may or may not mean things will be better for everyone or even for just monks or tanks.  It could mean they want people still whimpering over various nerfs to hang in there until SWG/EQ2 come out.  Could also mean they're really are working on balance issues.  I'll believe it when I see it.  Judging from the last patch, I think we can all see just how hard they're working on providing good fixes for EQ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twotribes>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 686<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/03 3:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shield upgrades-speculation?</span><hr size=1> I dont see how they can improve shield use for dual wielders without improving them for everyone that uses a shield, unless they are going to put in some awesome overpowering shields that are warrior, ranger, rogue only. Maybe Bard too.<br>
<br>
I for one cant see ever switching to a shield since my offhand epic gives 40 percent haste. I wont even use a 2 hander anymore. So I am stuck with ( well stuck isnt the word) one hand slash and Piercer ( my onehandblunt sucks) and only for main hand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=asotus007>Asotus007</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/03 2:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shield upgrades-speculation?</span><hr size=1> I agree Bjond. It is geared toward improving warrior tanking ability. I also think it is an attempt to bring the shield back into EverQuest. When was the last time you saw a warrior with a shield ? Exactly. <br>
 A similar 'adjustment' was made when the necessity of duel wielding made two handers obsolete for warriors. Added damage bonus, better ratio 2 handers ( not just for sk/pal ), punishing blow, PoP mobs that eat duel wielders with repostes ..... viola ! Two handed warriors are plentiful once more in the lands. Now it's the shields turn. The added AC of shields looks pretty attractive when they raise the 'softcap' 500-600 points <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Furious Bash Shields and one handed enraging blow will now be a viable option to two handing. Variety is good.<br>
